Verity creates integrity hashes for binary blobs.

Verity is the userspace component for dm-verity.  It creates integrity
hashes for a given filesystem image file.  For the details of the
design, see [1].  It is meant to be run in the build environment and not
on the target device.

[1] http://www.chromium.org/chromium-os/chromiumos-design-docs/verified-boot
